<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">
                                <gloss target="#t_AEC1">A.E.C.</gloss> Files (Historical Doc. No.
                                166)</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                    Director of the Office of Scientific Research and
                                    Development</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bush</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d325fn1">This
                                    letter was delivered to Busies office in Washington while Bush
                                    was in England, and he was informed of its contents by cable.
                                    Concerning the garble in the message as he received it, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_645">p.
                                    645</ref>.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-20">July 20,
                                    1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Van</hi>: While the Prime Minister was
                                here we discussed the whole question of exchange of information
                                regarding <gloss target="#t_TubeAlloys1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tube Alloys</hi></gloss>, including the
                                building project.</p>
                            <p>While I am mindful of the vital necessity for security in regard to
                                this, I feel that our understanding with the British encompasses the
                                complete exchange of all information.</p>
                            <p>I wish, therefore, that you would renew, in an inclusive manner, the
                                full exchange of information with the British Government regarding
                                    <gloss target="#t_TubeAlloys1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tube Alloys</hi></gloss>.</p>
                            <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D Roosevelt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>